Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
refinePlace(25.10)                                          refinePlace(25.10)

Name
       refinePlace - Corrects flawed cell locations and reports corrections or
       instance overlap problems

Syntax
       refinePlace

       [-help]

       [-area {lx ly ux uy}]

       [-eco {true|false}]

       [-inst <list_of_instances>]

       [-wire_length_reclaim {true|false}]

       Corrects  flawed  cell  locations  and  reports corrections or instance
       overlap problems. You do not need a fully placed design to run  refine-
       Place.  The  refinePlace command only makes changes if the placement is
       not legal, such as for instance overlap,  incorrect  orientation,  con-
       straint  violations, and placement/routing blockage violations. You can
       use the checkPlace command to highlight placement violations in the de-
       sign. The refinePlace command is called automatically  at  the  end  of
       each  major  super  command  such  as  place_opt_design, optDesign, and
       ccopt_design to ensure that the final placement is  violation-free.  If
       any  instances  are  moved manually, refinePlace can be run to legalize
       any cell placements that may have resulted in violations  due  to  this
       manual movement.

       To place unplaced instances, use the ecoPlace command.

       refinePlace  only  operates on the cells which have the 'placed' place-
       ment status.

       Note: You can also use setPlaceMode to specify parameters for this com-
       mand. If you use setPlaceMode, the parameters apply every time you  run
       refinePlace  in the current session, unless they are overwritten by the
       refinePlace settings.

       Note: refinePlace and other commands using refinePlace  API  honor  in-
       stance  padding  constraint  as  a hard rule if setPlaceMode -place_de-
       tail_honor_inst_pad is set to true.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information for each refinePlace parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man refinePlace

       -area {llx lly urx ury}
              Specifies refinePlace area.

              * llx: Specifies the area's lower left x coordinate.

              * lly: Specifies the area's lower left y coordinate.

              * urx: Specifies the area's upper right x coordinate.

              * ury: Specifies the area's upper right y coordinate.

              Note: The coordinates for the -area option should be provided in
              brackets, else the tool will report an error.

       -eco {true|false}
              Activates ECO mode for the post-route design.

              Default: false

              Note:  This  option  is  controlled  by  setPlaceMode -place_de-
              tail_eco_max_distance.

       -inst <list_of_instances>
              Legalizes the list of instances provided by the user. All  other
              instances are treated as fixed.

              Note:  This  option  is  controlled  by  setPlaceMode -place_de-
              tail_eco_max_distance.

       -wire_length_reclaim {true|false}
              Activates the wire length reclaim mode.

Command Order
       Use this command after finding an error with the checkPlace command.

Example
              * The following command refines the placement in  the  specified
                area:

                refinePlace -area {7.925 29.762 11.702 27.531}

